        <h3>Design</h3>
        <p>As I was going to be developing the site in addition to designing it, I decided to skip creating some low fidelity wireframes and immediately move to creating some high fidelity wireframes on Sketch. Seeing as the site was going to be no more than 3-4 pages, I had a good idea of how the layout of site should be based off of the requirements set by the founder:
            <ul>
                <li>Clear and concise call to action</li>
                <li>Highlight benefits of platform</li>
                <li>Contact/Pricing form for potential customers</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>I first began mocking up a couple examples of how the homepage and feature section should be laid out. I want to make sure I created responsive and reusable design elements/characteristics allowing me to writing resusable HTML and CSS elsewhere on the site. </p>
    </div>
